.TH LIBRJSS 3 "17 Jul 2026" "0.3.0" "librjss API Manual"
.SH NAME
librjss \- Rust library for cookie-based session authentication
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
Cargo.toml:
    [dependencies]
    librjss = { git = "https://github.com/mroczect/librjss.git" }

Rust source:
    use librjss::api::AuthManager;
    use librjss::handler::config::AuthConfig;
    use librjss::handler::session_store::MemorySessionStore;
    use librjss::handler::types::{Credentials, UserProvider, SessionStore};
    use std::sync::Arc;
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B librjss
is a protocol-agnostic, framework-agnostic Rust library that provides
building blocks for cookie-based session authentication. It does not
depend on any specific web framework. It defines traits for user
lookup and session storage and offers a ready-to-use
.B AuthManager
that orchestrates the authentication lifecycle.

The library is structured into two main modules:
.B api
(high-level manager and cookie helpers) and
.B handler
(lower-level types, configuration, error types, session store
implementation, and environment loading).

.SH MODULES
.SS api
.B api::AuthManager
is the central coordinator. It is constructed with an
.B AuthConfig ,
a
.B UserProvider ,
and a
.B SessionStore .
It exposes methods to login, logout, validate, create, and destroy sessions.
.B api::auth::cookies
contains functions to create, parse, and delete session cookies.
.B api::auth::session
contains low-level session creation, validation, and destruction logic.
.SS handler
.B handler::config
provides
.B AuthConfig
(defaults, builder with validation, SameSite enum).
.B handler::env
implements
.B AuthConfig::from_env()
to read configuration from environment variables.
.B handler::error
defines the
.B AuthError
enum with status code mapping and JSON body generation.
.B handler::session_store
contains a
.B MemorySessionStore ,
an in-memory session store implementation suitable for development and testing.
.B handler::types
contains all core data types and traits:
.BR SessionId ,
.BR Credentials ,
.BR UserInfo ,
.BR SessionInfo ,
.BR HttpResponse ,
.BR UserProvider ,
and
.BR SessionStore .

.SH DATA TYPES
.TP
.B SessionId
A newtype wrapper over String representing a session identifier.
Construct with
.BR SessionId::new(id) .
Use
.B .as_str()
to get a &str. Implements Display, Eq, Hash, Serialize, Deserialize.
.TP
.B Credentials
Holds
.B username: String
and
.B password: String
used for login.
.TP
.B UserInfo
Returned from
.BR UserProvider::authenticate() .
Fields:
.BR user_id: String ,
.B extra: serde_json::Value
(arbitrary claims).
.TP
.B SessionInfo
Session record stored in the session store. Fields:
.BR user_id: String ,
.B data: serde_json::Value ,
.BR issued_at: OffsetDateTime ,
.BR expires_at: OffsetDateTime ,
.BR idle_deadline: Option<OffsetDateTime> .
.TP
.B HttpResponse
A minimal HTTP response decoupled from any framework.
Constructors:
.BR HttpResponse::new(status, body) ,
.BR HttpResponse::json(status, json_value) .
Builder:
.B .with_header(key, value)
. Fields:
.BR status: http::StatusCode ,
.BR headers: Vec<(String, String)> ,
.BR body: String .
.SH TRAITS
.TP
.B UserProvider
async trait that must be implemented for user authentication.
.nf
    async fn authenticate(&self, creds: &Credentials) -> Result<UserInfo, AuthError>
    async fn get_user_by_id(&self, user_id: &str) -> Result<Option<UserInfo>, AuthError>
.fi
.TP
.B SessionStore
async trait for session persistence.
.nf
    async fn save(&self, id: &SessionId, info: &SessionInfo) -> Result<(), AuthError>
    async fn load(&self, id: &SessionId) -> Result<Option<SessionInfo>, AuthError>
    async fn delete(&self, id: &SessionId) -> Result<(), AuthError>
    async fn cleanup(&self) -> Result<(), AuthError>
.fi
.SH CONFIGURATION
.B AuthConfig
can be created using defaults, the builder pattern, or from environment.
.TS
tab(|);
l l.
Default values:
cookie_name|"sid"
cookie_path|"/"
cookie_domain|None
cookie_secure|true
cookie_http_only|true
cookie_same_site|SameSite::Lax
session_lifetime|24 hours
session_idle_timeout|None
login_url|None
logout_redirect_url|None
.TE

.B AuthConfigBuilder
methods: .cookie_name(), .cookie_path(), .cookie_domain(), .cookie_secure(),
.cookie_http_only(), .cookie_same_site(), .session_lifetime(),
.session_idle_timeout(), .login_url(), .logout_redirect_url().
Finalize with
.B .build() -> Result<AuthConfig, AuthError>
which validates lifetime > 0 and cookie_name non-empty.

.B SameSite
enum variants: Strict, Lax (default), None.

.SH ENVIRONMENT
.B AuthConfig::from_env()
reads these optional variables (all have defaults):
.TP
.B AUTH_COOKIE_NAME
(default "sid")
.TP
.B AUTH_COOKIE_PATH
(default "/")
.TP
.B AUTH_COOKIE_DOMAIN
(optional)
.TP
.B AUTH_COOKIE_SECURE
"true"/"false" (default "true")
.TP
.B AUTH_COOKIE_HTTP_ONLY
"true"/"false" (default "true")
.TP
.B AUTH_COOKIE_SAME_SITE
"Strict"/"Lax"/"None" (default "Lax")
.TP
.B AUTH_SESSION_LIFETIME
integer seconds (default 86400)
.TP
.B AUTH_SESSION_IDLE_TIMEOUT
integer seconds (optional)
.TP
.B AUTH_LOGIN_URL
optional URL string
.TP
.B AUTH_LOGOUT_REDIRECT_URL
optional URL string

.SH ERROR HANDLING
.B AuthError
enum variants:
.RS
.TP
.B Config(String)
Configuration error.
.TP
.B InvalidCredentials
Bad username/password.
.TP
.B AccountLocked { until: String }
Account locked.
.TP
.B SessionExpired
Session expired.
.TP
.B SessionNotFound
Session ID not found.
.TP
.B Internal(String)
Internal error.
.TP
.B Serialization(String)
Serialization error.
.RE
Methods:
.TP
.B .status_code() -> http::StatusCode
Maps variant to HTTP status (500, 401, 403).
.TP
.B .to_json_body() -> serde_json::Value
Returns {"error":"message"}.

.SH SESSION STORE
.B MemorySessionStore
in-memory implementation for development/testing.
.nf
    let store = MemorySessionStore::new();
.fi
Implements
.B SessionStore
with async RwLock<HashMap>.
.B cleanup()
removes sessions where expires_at <= now.

.SH AUTHMANAGER API
.B AuthManager::new(config, user_provider, session_store)
.TP
.B login(credentials) -> Result<HttpResponse, AuthError>
Validates non-empty credentials, calls user_provider.authenticate(),
creates session, returns 200 with Set-Cookie and JSON body.
.TP
.B logout(session_id: Option<&SessionId>) -> Result<HttpResponse, AuthError>
Destroys session (if provided), returns clearance cookie and 200 or redirect.
.TP
.B validate_session(session_id) -> Result<SessionInfo, AuthError>
Checks expiry and idle timeout, deletes expired sessions.
.TP
.B create_session(user_info) -> Result<(SessionId, SessionInfo), AuthError>
Directly creates a session, returns id and info.
.TP
.B destroy_session(session_id) -> Result<(), AuthError>
Deletes session from store.

.SH COOKIE FUNCTIONS (api::auth::cookies)
.TP
.B create_session_cookie(session_id, config) -> Cookie
Builds cookie with name, path, domain, secure, httpOnly, SameSite, max_age.
.TP
.B parse_session_id_from_cookie(cookie_header, config) -> Option<SessionId>
Extracts session ID from Cookie header string.
.TP
.B create_removal_cookie(config) -> Cookie
Returns empty cookie with max_age=0 to clear session.

.SH SESSION FUNCTIONS (api::auth::session)
.TP
.B generate_session_id() -> SessionId
32-character alphanumeric random string.
.TP
.B create_session(store, config, user_info) -> Result<(SessionId, SessionInfo), AuthError>
Generates ID, sets timestamps, saves.
.TP
.B validate_session(store, config, id) -> Result<SessionInfo, AuthError>
Validates and auto-deletes expired sessions.
.TP
.B destroy_session(store, id) -> Result<(), AuthError>
Deletes session.

.SH EXAMPLE
A minimal actix-web integration:
.nf
use librjss::api::AuthManager;
use librjss::handler::config::AuthConfig;
use librjss::handler::session_store::MemorySessionStore;
use librjss::handler::types::{Credentials, UserProvider, UserInfo, AuthError};
use std::sync::Arc;

struct MyProvider;
#[async_trait]
impl UserProvider for MyProvider {
    async fn authenticate(&self, c: &Credentials) -> Result<UserInfo, AuthError> {
        if c.username == "admin" && c.password == "pass" {
            Ok(UserInfo { user_id: "admin".into(), extra: serde_json::json!({}) })
        } else {
            Err(AuthError::InvalidCredentials)
        }
    }
    async fn get_user_by_id(&self, id: &str) -> Result<Option<UserInfo>, AuthError> {
        Ok(None)
    }
}

let config = AuthConfig::builder().cookie_name("sid".into())
    .session_lifetime(time::Duration::hours(2)).build().unwrap();
let manager = AuthManager::new(config, Arc::new(MyProvider), Arc::new(MemorySessionStore::new()));

// In an actix handler:
async fn login(state: web::Data<AppState>, body: web::Json<LoginReq>) -> HttpResponse {
    let resp = state.manager.login(Credentials { username: body.user.clone(), password: body.pass.clone() }).await;
    // convert librjss::HttpResponse to actix_web::HttpResponse ...
}
.fi

